HEADWORD: pachyderm
<hw>pach"y*derm</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧k"⟦icr⟧*d⟦etil⟧rm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>pachyderme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
of various nonruminant hoofed mammals having very thick skin, including
the <stype>elephant</stype>, <stype>rhinoceros</stype>, and
<stype>hippopotamus</stype>, one of the Pachydermata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

